Requirements

1.1 Functional Requirements The Smart Library Management System (SLMS) intends to provide the following functions: Member Functions

Login using username and password.
View available books.
Borrow books (maximum of 5 books at a time).
Return borrowed books.
Reserve books that are currently borrowed.
View book status (Available, Borrowed, Reserved). Librarian Functions
Add new books to the system.
View all books.
Manage book records. Administrator Functions
Set borrowing limits.
Manage system settings.
1.2 Non-Functional Requirements

The system must be implemented in C++.
The system must follow Object-Oriented principles.
The system must demonstrate: o Inheritance o Encapsulation o Polymorphism
The system must run in a console environment.
The system must respond quickly to borrow and reserve actions.
